  <div id="about" class="content">
    <h1> About </h1>

    <p>
      It seems like there's a learning curve to modern Linux:
      It's relatively easy to
      <a href="https://ubuntu.com/tutorials/tutorial-create-a-usb-stick-on-windows#1-overview"> install Ubuntu from a thumb drive</a>
      and then get on the web, but to learn how to do...
      <i> what it does... </i> requires an enormous amount of learning.
      I'm not sure that the volume of information can be changed, but the process of learning it could be made easier.
    </p>

    <p>
      This site is intended to provide new-ish Linux users with accurate and down-to-earth explanations of concepts pervasive throughout
      the open-source ecosystem&mdash; or references to them.
      Please send questions, comments, corrections and/or recommendations to <a href="mailto:josh-591536@gmail.com">Josh Timmons</a>.
      I'd love to hear from you!
      Also, contributions welcome!
    </p>

    <p>
      Enjoy!
    </p>

